      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2008 BMW M3 featuring the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS steplessly variable valve timing to deliver linear power delivery up to its 8,400 RPM redline. The chassis remains composed through high-lateral G-loads thanks to M-specific suspension geometry and a rigid subframe, while the M Variable Differential Lock ensures optimal torque distribution across the rear axle. This example features a crisp 6-speed manual transmission with a short-throw shifter for precise engagement. Recent service includes a cooling system refresh and a comprehensive rod bearing analysis, ensuring the internal tolerances remain within spec. While the exterior exhibits minor road patina consistent with its age, the mechanical integrity is robust, offering a visceral, analog steering response and a stellar power-to-weight ratio.",
